text: Guamaggiore (Gomajòri) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sud Sardegna in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 984 people lived there. Its area is 16.8 km². It is 199 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of South Sardinia
title: Guamaggiore
